-- Mexico Stocks: Grupo Financiero Banorte, Grupo Elektra
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-04-18T20:48:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-18/mexico-stocks-grupo-financiero-banorte-grupo-elektra.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC  index  fell 0.1 percent to 39,330.12.  Grupo Financiero Banorte SAB (GFNORTEO)  , a Mexican
lender, fell 4 percent to 60.73 pesos. The company had its
recommendation cut to “neutral” from “overweight” at
JPMorgan Chase & Co., according to a research note dated today.  Grupo Elektra SA (ELEKTRA* MM), the banking and retail
company controlled by billionaire  Ricardo Salinas , climbed 4.6
percent to 919.83 pesos. Elektra said today it plans to start
brokerage operations with a subsidiary called Punto Casa de
Bolsa. Elektra has been rebounding from a three-day selloff that
ended April 16. The exchange published new rules on April 11
that may cut the company’s weight in the benchmark index in
half, according to a research note from  Banco Santander SA. (SAN)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
